From 7677844677916ff16d18b1c67c2dec4389cf0dc3 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Steve <steventhanhtuan@gmail.com>
Date: Tue, 14 Jul 2026 17:37:27 +0700
Subject: [PATCH 10/17] task4: consolidate publication.py mirror/harvest cores,
 no behavior change

_mirror_into_view now holds the atomic write, three-way clobber guard,
prune rule and manifest save once for both notes and skills (index.md
regenerates unconditionally via an explicit parameter). harvest_drafts
and harvest_skills share one walker with glob/exclude/transform hooks.
Dead _VERDICT_FRONTMATTER_FIELDS removed; duplicated contract docstrings
replaced with cross-references to one canonical home. 977 -> 949 lines;
gate tests byte-identical and green (62), full suite 691 passed.

Harvest now decodes drafts as utf-8 explicitly where the old path used
the locale default; the writer always emits utf-8, so this pins the
intended encoding rather than changing behavior.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Fable 5 <noreply@anthropic.com>
